The Islamic Education Trust (IET), Nurul Islam and Aminu Musa Abdulsalam (AMA) Foundation at the weekend jointly launched the pilot phase of Almajarai vocational training programme. This partnership according to a statement by the Communication Officer, IET, Suleiman Murkthar, was to ensure sustainable solutions to issue of Almajirai children in Northern Nigeria. Mukhtar said that the intervention was aimed at developing a culturally and religiously sensitive educational programme which could rapidly enhance the potential and capacity of the Almajarai youth for a vocational career.